article.headline: Tulsa 75, Arkansas St. 59
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Jerome Jordan and Glenn Andrews scored 14 points each as Tulsa overpowered Arkansas State 75-59 on Friday. Jordan, a 6-10 sophomore who also had seven rebounds and four blocks, converted lob passes for dunks twice in a 10-2 Tulsa run that lifted the Golden Hurricane to a 70-50 lead with 3:27 to play. Andrews, a 6-4 freshman, hit four of six shots and five of six free throws for Tulsa (2-1). The Golden Hurricane outpaced the Indians on the boards 43-27, led by a career-high 15 rebounds from forward Calvin Walls. Ryan Wedel scored 16 points for Arkansas State (0-2), which shot just 35.5 percent from the field. Leading scorer Adrian Banks was limited to 11 points on four-of-14 shooting and Shawn Morgan added 10 points. Despite 22 turnovers, Tulsa took a 32-22 lead into halftime and never trailed after that. A 3-pointer by freshman Justin Hurtt put TU ahead 51-31 with 13:02 to play, but Arkansas State fought back to get within 60-46. Jordan then led another Tulsa surge that put the game away.
